		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />32M on LoROM is easy:
<br />
<br />ROM A0-A14 = CPU A0-14
<br />ROM A15-21 = CPU A16-22
<br />
<br />Since there are 24 address lines you could even have a 64M LoROM game, but you wouldn't be able to use 64 KiB in banks $7E-7F IIRC due to WRAM mapping and only half the ROM could be accessed as FastROM.
<br />
<br />I'm not sure if mixed LoROM/HiROM is used on any games, but it's only necessary when you have a game over 32M and you want all code to run FastROM. Perhaps Tales of Phantasia does it. Basically in that configuration a 32M ROM is wired as HiROM, a &lt;=32M as LoROM, then the decoder selects them based on A22.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


